# LegacyLens — Cursor AI Rules
# These rules guide Cursor's AI code generation for this entire project.
# Cursor reads this file for every file in the workspace.

## Project Overview

LegacyLens is a RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) system that answers natural-language
questions about legacy COBOL code. Think of it as Google Search, but for old business code.

- Backend: Python 3.12, FastAPI, LangChain (selective), Pydantic v2, pytest
- Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS, NextAuth.js
- Vector DB: Pinecone (serverless, cosine similarity, 1536 dims)
- Embeddings: OpenAI text-embedding-3-small
- LLM: GPT-4o-mini (streaming answers via SSE)
- Deployment: Railway (backend, port 8000) + Vercel (frontend, port 3000)

---

## Python Code Style

### Language Features
- Python 3.12 features are allowed: match statements, `type X = ...` syntax
- Use `str | None` instead of `Optional[str]`
- Use `list[str]` instead of `List[str]`, `dict[str, Any]` instead of `Dict[str, Any]`
- Use `pathlib.Path` instead of `os.path` for all file system operations
- Use `logging.getLogger(__name__)` instead of `print()` for all output

### Type Annotations
- All functions must have complete type annotations (parameters + return type)
- All class attributes must have type annotations
- Pydantic v2 syntax: use `model_validator`, `field_validator` (not the old `validator`)
- Never use bare `Any` without a comment explaining why it's unavoidable

### Async
- All FastAPI endpoints must be `async def` — synchronous endpoints are not allowed
- Use `asyncio.gather()` for parallel external API calls (don't call them one at a time)

### Formatting
- Line length: 88 characters (ruff default)
- Quotes: double quotes
- Indentation: 4 spaces

---

## TypeScript Code Style

### Strictness
- Strict TypeScript only — no implicit `any`, no `any` without a comment
- Use `type` for object shapes, `interface` for extendable contracts
- Use `const` assertions where values won't change
- Use consistent-type-imports: `import type { Foo } from './foo'` for type-only imports

### Functions and Components
- Arrow function components: `const MyComponent = () => { ... }`
- Named exports only — except Next.js page/layout files (which require default exports)
- Explicit return types for non-trivial functions

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS for all styling — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Use `clsx` or `cn()` utility for conditional class names

### No Console
- No `console.log` in production code — use `console.error` only for genuine errors

