## Frontend Architecture Patterns

### API Client Pattern (src/lib/api.ts)
```typescript
// All backend calls go through this file — never use raw fetch() in components.
// This gives us one place to add auth headers, handle errors, and change the base URL.

const API_BASE = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL ?? 'http://localhost:8000'

export async function queryCode(
  query: string,
  token: string,
): Promise<QueryResponse> {
  const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE}/api/v1/query`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({ query }),
  })

  if (!response.ok) {
    // Throw a typed error so callers can handle it properly
    throw new ApiError(response.status, await response.text())
  }

  return response.json() as Promise<QueryResponse>
}
```

### Server vs Client Component Decision
```
// Use Server Component (no 'use client') when:
// - Fetching initial data on page load
// - No user interaction needed (not a button, form, or click handler)
// - No browser-only APIs (no window, localStorage, etc.)

// Use Client Component ('use client') when:
// - User clicks, types, or interacts with the component
// - Using React hooks (useState, useEffect, useRef)
// - Showing real-time streaming updates
// - Using browser APIs
```

