## Security Rules

- NEVER hardcode API keys, secrets, or tokens anywhere in the code
- Backend secrets: load from environment via `app/config.py` Settings class
- Frontend secrets: never put secrets in frontend code or `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variables
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_` variables are visible to the browser — only use for non-sensitive config
- CORS: restrict to `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` only — no wildcard (`*`) in production
- Auth tokens: stored in httpOnly cookies (set by NextAuth) — never in localStorage

---

## Performance Rules

- Batch OpenAI embedding calls — never embed one chunk at a time (use batches of 100)
- Use `asyncio.gather()` for parallel external API calls
- Cache the Pinecone client instance with `@lru_cache` — don't recreate on every request
- Limit retrieved context to top 5 chunks — avoids hitting GPT-4o-mini's context limit
- Enable streaming for answer generation — users see results immediately instead of waiting

---

## Do Not

- Do not use `any` in TypeScript without a comment
- Do not use `print()` in Python — use `logging`
- Do not make real OpenAI or Pinecone calls in unit tests — mock them
- Do not commit `.env` or `.env.local`
- Do not create TODO comments — open a GitHub issue instead
- Do not suppress linting without a reason comment (`# noqa: <code>  # reason here`)
- Do not write synchronous FastAPI endpoints
- Do not import FastAPI types into `app/core/` modules
